author: The Current
description:
Watch Mt. Joy's performance of "Lucy" in studio
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

Spanning the summer of 2025, Los Angeles-based band Mt. Joy have experienced what singer/guitarist Matt Quinn describes as “the best tour we've ever had.” When their tour took them to the Twin Cities, Mt. Joy visited The Current studio to play songs from a couple of their albums. Watch and listen to a performance of "Lucy" above.

Musicians
Michael Byrnes – bass
Sam Cooper – guitar
Sotiris Eliopoulos – drums
Jackie Miclau – keyboards
Matt Quinn – vocals, guitar

author: The Current
description:
Danny Brown stopped by The Current and talked with host Zach McCormick about his newfound writing process for his latest album ‘Stardust.’

Danny Brown performed with @underscores and @femtanylll at Uptown Theater in Minneapolis on Tuesday, Nov. 18.
title: Danny Brown on the evolution of his writing style #dannybrown #interview #shorts #rap #bars

author: The Current
description:
To celebrate The Current’s 20th Anniversary, The Current’s Live Sessions Vault unlocks never-before-seen live performance videos of bands and artists who have played in our iconic studio. 

Watch to see the full session of The Cactus Blossoms featuring previously unreleased footage, from when they visited The Current studio back in 2013.

Songs Performed

00:02:56 You Gotta Change Your Ways or Die
